== Bond Types ==
* [[Types of bonds|https://www.finra.org/investors/types-bonds]]
** '''[[U.S. Treasury Securities|https://www.finra.org/investors/us-treasury-securities]]''' (T-bills, T-notes, T-bonds): U.S. Treasury securities ("Treasuries") are issued by the federal government and are considered to be among the safest investments you can make, because all Treasury securities are backed by the "full faith and credit" of the U.S. government

** '''[[U.S. Savings Bonds|https://www.finra.org/investors/us-savings-bonds]]''': Savings bonds are issued by the federal government and may be purchased for an investment as low as $25

** '''[[TIPS and STRIPS|https://www.finra.org/investors/tips-and-strips]]''': TIPS shelter you from inflation risk because their principal is adjusted semiannually based on changes in the Consumer Price Index-Urban Consumers, a widely used measure of inflation. STRIPS are a different type of Treasury bond that let investors hold and trade the individual interest and principal components of eligible Treasury notes and bonds as separate securities. 

** '''[[Mortgage-Backed Securities (MBS)|https://www.finra.org/investors/mortgage-backed-securities]]''': secured by home and other real estate loans; they are created when a number of these loans, usually with similar characteristics, are pooled together. 

** '''[[Agency Securities|https://www.finra.org/investors/agency-securities]]''': "Agencies" is a term used to describe bonds issued or guaranteed by U.S. federal government agencies and bonds issued by government-sponsored enterprises (GSEs)—corporations created by Congress to foster a public purpose.

** '''[[Municipal Bonds|https://www.finra.org/investors/municipal-bonds]]''': Municipal securities, or "munis," are bonds issued by states, cities, counties and other governmental entities to raise money to build roads, schools and a host of other projects for the public good.

** '''[[Corporate Bonds|https://www.finra.org/investors/corporate-bonds]]''': Companies issue corporate bonds to raise money for capital expenditures, operations and acquisitions. Corporate bonds are issued by all types of businesses, and are segmented into major industry groups.

** '''[[International and Emerging Markets Bonds|https://www.finra.org/investors/international-and-emerging-markets-bonds]]''': These are bonds issued by foreign governments and companies. Since interest rate movements may differ from country to country, international bonds are another way to diversify your portfolio, but carry their own set of risks. 

